<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:geo="http://www.w3.org/2003/01/geo/wgs84_pos#" xmlns:georss="http://www.georss.org/georss" xmlns:slash="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/" xmlns:sy="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/" xmlns:wfw="http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/"><channel><title>流动数据</title><atom:link href="https://flowingdata.com/feed/" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><link/> https://flowingdata.com<description>数量优势</description><lastbuilddate>2024 年 7 月 3 日，星期三 01:24:00 +0000</lastbuilddate><language> en-US</language><sy:updateperiod>每小时</sy:updateperiod><sy:updatefrequency>1</sy:updatefrequency><generator> https://wordpress.org/?v=6.5.5</generator><site xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 1938889</site><item><title>谷歌街景之后看世界</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/03/seeing-the-world-after-google-streetview/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Wed, 03 Jul 2024 07:13:52 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Maps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Visualization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Streetview]]></category><category><![CDATA[New York Times]]></category><category><![CDATA[Trevor Rainbolt]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=74531 </guid><description><![CDATA[Trevor Rainbolt is really good at geolocating a place given a single frame&#8230;<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/google-streetview/" rel="tag">谷歌街景</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/new-york-times/" rel="tag">纽约时报</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/trevor-rainbolt/" rel="tag">特雷弗·雷恩博尔特</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> Trevor Rainbolt <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2023/03/14/finding-the-physical-location-in-an-online-video-via-google-maps-clues/">非常擅长根据 Google 街景中的单个帧对地点进行地理定位</a>。他过去只在办公桌上直播，但现在他正在探索物理世界。 <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/19/magazine/trevor-rainbolt-geoguessr-google-maps.html?unlocked_article_code=1.200.zUNN.jXIx4MadUkh6&#038;smid=url-share">托马斯·韦伯 (Tomas Weber) 为《纽约时报》介绍了 Rainbolt 的扩展观点</a>。</p><blockquote><p> 《Rainbolt》最平庸的时刻现在带有一点顿悟和认可的酊剂。事实证明，如果你在电脑上着迷于它的质地和色调，那么第一次触摸泰国草会更加激动人心：这是与一位长期记者面对面会面的兴奋，是与一位资深记者的第一次约会。老暗恋。 Rainbolt 利用互联网的制图技术来增强世界的强度，将虚拟与现实融合在一起，使两者都更加令人愉悦。去年七月，他在一段视频中宣布，他很快就会登上乞力马扎罗山，他说：“如果有山，抑郁症就不可能是真的。”他的路线：谷歌街景相机十年前攀登的路线。</p></blockquote><p>数据为旅程提供信息。</p><p>另请参阅：<a href="https://flowingdata.com/2011/11/24/touching-google-streetview-stop-motion/">地址近似</a>，定格动画冒险。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/google-streetview/" rel="tag">谷歌街景</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/new-york-times/" rel="tag">纽约时报</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/trevor-rainbolt/" rel="tag">特雷弗·雷恩博尔特</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 74531</post-id></item><item><title>流动数据 17</title><link/> https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/flowingdata-at-17/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Tue, 02 Jul 2024 14:23:48 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Site News]]></category><category><![CDATA[birthday]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=74552 </guid><description><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/flowingdata-at-17/"><img width="750" height="438" src="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?w=822&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 822w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=210%2C123&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 210w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=768%2C448&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="74576" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/flowingdata-at-17/keep-on-going/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=822%2C480&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="822,480" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="keep-on-going" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=822%2C480&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" tabindex="0" role="button" /></a></p>上周标志着互联网这个小角落运行 17 周年……<p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/birthday/" rel="tag">生日</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p> <a href="https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/flowingdata-at-17/"><img width="750" height="438" src="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?w=822&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 822w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 750w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=210%2C123&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 210w, https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?resize=768%2C448&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" data-attachment-id="74576" data-permalink="https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/flowingdata-at-17/keep-on-going/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=822%2C480&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="822,480" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="keep-on-going" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=750%2C438&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/keep-on-going.jpg?fit=822%2C480&amp;quality=89&amp;ssl=1" tabindex="0" role="button" /></a></p><p>上周标志着互联网这个小角落在数据可视化方面的运行 17 周年。感谢<a href="https://flowingdata.com/membership/">FlowingData 过去和现在的成员</a>。谢谢阅读。没有你们，这个网站就不存在。</p><p>感觉并没有那么久，但也很难记得我没有在 FlowingData 上工作的时候。</p><p>在撰写<a href="https://book.flowingdata.com/">《Visualize This》</a>第二版时，我想起了这些年来可视化的变化。不同的工具、不同的设备和不同的数据集。经过多年制作图表后，我对数据和可视化的看法有所不同。</p><p>可视化的范围不同。它已经变得更好，超越了快速分析。</p><p>互联网则不同。为了结束 FlowingData 两周年纪念日，我感谢读者通过 Twitter、Digg 和 del.icio.us 向我发送链接，这些链接如今已与最初的形式相去甚远。</p><p>尽管如此，在这个网站上工作对我来说还是很有趣的。我仍然喜欢探索数据。也许比我刚开始的时候更重要。我仍然对人们如何创造性地处理数据感到兴奋。我仍然感谢互联网之神让我做到了这一点。</p><p>再次感谢。</p><p>到明年。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/birthday/" rel="tag">生日</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 74552</post-id></item><item><title>缩小到原子大小</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/02/shrinking-down-to-the-size-of-an-atom/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Tue, 02 Jul 2024 07:32:37 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Infographics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Epic Spaceman]]></category><category><![CDATA[scale]]></category><category><![CDATA[small]]></category><guid ispermalink="false"> https://flowingdata.com/?p=74527 </guid><description><![CDATA[In a different take on showing the scale of very tiny things, Epic&#8230;<p><strong>标签:</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/epic-spaceman/" rel="tag">史诗太空人</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/scale/" rel="tag">规模</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/small/" rel="tag">小</a></p>]]>; </description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="iframe-container"><iframe class="youtube-player" width="1090" height="614" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rn9dkV4sVYQ?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent" allowfullscreen="true" style="border:0;" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox"></iframe></p><p> 《Epic Spaceman》以不同的方式展示了非常微小的物体的尺寸，它从人类大小开始，每 21 秒缩小十倍。</p><p><strong>标签:</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/epic-spaceman/" rel="tag">史诗太空人</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/scale/" rel="tag">规模</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/small/" rel="tag">小</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 74527</post-id></item><item><title>世界领导人和他们所服务的人群之间的年龄差异</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2024/07/01/age-differences- Between-world-leaders-and-the-populations-they-serve/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Mon, 01 Jul 2024 08:28:21 +0000</pubDate> <category><![CDATA[Statistical Visual